track_notes: For the adventurous who drive all the way up to Onne on a narrow gravel road, the hike is just under an hour on a T2 trail. Thanks to Kurt HB9AFI for his extensive local knowledge and tips on being able to drive up this far.
An easier drive that avoids the narrow gravel road, hike takes about 1.5 hours.
The hike from here takes approx 2 hours. This is also the best parking for VS-239 (40 minute hike) and VS-102 (also a 40 minute hike). Ambitious activators have done all 3 summits in one day.
